thread.title: Nick Chubb Carted Off Field After Possible Knee Injury
thread.title_full: Nick Chubb Carted Off Field After Possible Knee Injury

author: Kelly Terez
title: Nick Chubb Carted Off Field After Possible Knee Injury
text:
Share Article 
Todd Kirkland/Getty Images (KNOXVILLE, Tenn.) -- Nick Chubb may have a serious knee injury after Saturday's game against Tennessee. 
The Georgia sophomore running back fell on his left leg awkwardly when he was tackled out of bounds, and it bent at a severe angle. 
According to ESPN , as Chub moved with support, he passed out in the arms of helpers and a cart was brought in to move him off the field. 
He regained consciousness at some point when he was being wheeled off, said ESPN. 
Chubb is a Heisman Trophy candidate and currently ranks second in the SEC this season.
